        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>The &#34;Jewish Messenger&#44;&#34;¬ù<lb/>
                92 Walker Street.<lb/></p>
            <p>New York&#44; Nov 17 1879<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Friend&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>I am glad I left 14. alone.  I<lb/> have not Lalle&#39;s emendations.  &#91;&#63;&#93;chender<lb/> has not answered yet.  I did not write<lb/> to Berliner.  Those German fellows are<lb/> terribly busy &#38; neglect their correspondents.<lb/></p>
            <p>This angle&#45;handed work<lb/> here&#8212;for the present.  Thank God&#44;<lb/> in &#91;&#63;&#93;s&#39; time when the children<lb/> became men &#38; women&#44; I may have an<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93;bal congregation.  May the dream be<lb/> realized &#38; not rudely be broken<lb/> like so many other visions of young<lb/> men.  Motives of delicacy have<lb/> hitherto restrained me from referring<lb/> to the E. B&#39;way syn. &#91;&#63;&#93; which is<lb/> being &#91;&#63;&#93;rred on steadily&#44; with excellent<lb/> results&#44; &#38; in which I shall very<lb/> soon open classes in Mishna&#44;<lb/> Bible &#38; Jewish History&#44; for Sabbaths<lb/> &#40;12&#45;2&#41;.  But now since I suggested to<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>&#91;&#63;&#93; to start me in his syn.&#44; I can refer to<lb/> that without being suspected of personal<lb/> advertisement.  On Sabbath last&#44; I attended<lb/> the service there &#40;I preach once a month&#41;<lb/> &#38; the sight was superb.  I have never<lb/> seen such an assemblage of children<lb/> in a synagogue for worship.  There were<lb/> nearly 400 &#38; the wall was lined<lb/> with grown people.  &#91;&#63;&#93; spoke well<lb/> &#38; to the point.  Oh&#44; his blessed<lb/> work&#44; which shall bring its<lb/> fruition in time.  As soon as<lb/> one year more passes&#44; &#38; the boys<lb/> and girls are a little maturer&#44; there<lb/> are many ways of improving the<lb/> method in use.  Their English literature<lb/> must be taught as well &#38; Sunday evenings<lb/> I shall utilize for social purposes<lb/> making the little ones read&#44; sing <del>play</del>&#44; &#38; dance &#38; have then parents at<lb/> hand.  This is the best way to<lb/> Amer. them.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours&#44;<lb/> 
                A S Isaacs<lb/>
                Rev. S. Morais<lb/></p>
        </body>
